author: THE ASSOCIATED PRESS
title: East Roundup: Quarterback Sets Records in Penn State Win
text: Quarterback Sets Records in Penn State Win By THE ASSOCIATED PRESS Christian Hackenberg threw for 315 yards and three touchdowns, and Penn State (6-2, 3-1 Big Ten) beat Maryland (2-5, 0-3), 31-30, in Baltimore on Saturday to spoil the debut of the interim coach Mike Locksley. Hackenberg displaced Zach Mills as the programâ€™s career leader in completions (608) and passing yards (7,453). DARTMOUTH 13, COLUMBIA 9 Dalyn Williams threw for 235 yards and a touchdown, and Dartmouth (6-0, 3-0 Ivy League) overcame a penalty-filled performance to beat visiting Columbia (1-5, 0-3). FORDHAM 59, LEHIGH 42 Chase Edmonds had 31 carries and a Patriot League record 347 yards as Fordham (7-1, 3-0) held off visiting Lehigh (3-4, 1-1). NAVY 31, TULANE 14 Navy quarterback Keenan Reynolds ran for two touchdowns, and the Midshipmen (5-1, 3-0 American Athletic Conference) forced three straight turnovers in the second half for a victory at home over Tulane (2-5, 1-3). RICE 38, ARMY 31 A 13-yard pass from Driphus Jackson to Zach Wright was just what Rice (4-3) needed for a victory at home over Army (2-6). LOUISVILLE 17, B.C. 14 Lamar Jackson ran for a short touchdown and passed for 230 yards, and Louisville (3-4, 2-2 Atlantic Coast Conference) made a big defensive stand late to preserve a victory over visiting Boston College (3-5, 0-5). HARVARD 42, PRINCETON 7 Scott Hosch threw for a career-high 437 yards and two touchdowns and ran for another score as host Harvard (6-0, 3-0 Ivy) beat Princeton (4-2, 1-2). Loading...
